<Link id="l00548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="548"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is useful when introducing indirection via a stub function at link time</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="549"><Highlight kind="comment">/// without compiler support. If a function pointer is formed without a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="550"><Highlight kind="comment">/// relocation, e.g. in the definition of \\c foo</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="554"><Highlight kind="comment">///   leaq -7(%rip), rax # form pointer to &#95;foo without relocation</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="555"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#95;bar:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="556"><Highlight kind="comment">///   leaq (%rip), %rax  # uses X86&#95;64&#95;RELOC&#95;SIGNED to &#39;&#95;foo&#39;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00557" /><CodeLine lineNumber="557"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endcode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00558" /><CodeLine lineNumber="558"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00559" /><CodeLine lineNumber="559"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the pointer to \\c &#95;foo computed by \\c &#95;foo and \\c &#95;bar may differ if we</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00560" /><CodeLine lineNumber="560"><Highlight kind="comment">/// introduce a stub for &#95;foo. If the pointer is used as a key, this may be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00561" /><CodeLine lineNumber="561"><Highlight kind="comment">/// observable to the program. This pass will attempt to introduce the missing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00562" /><CodeLine lineNumber="562"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &quot;self-relocation&quot; on the leaq instruction.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00563" /><CodeLine lineNumber="563"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00564" /><CodeLine lineNumber="564"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is based on disassembly and should be considered &quot;best effort&quot;. It may</Highlight></CodeLine>
